com.j2bugzilla.base

Class Bug

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.j2bugzilla.base.Bug

  • public class Bug
extends Object
    This class encapsulates all information about a bug report posted on a Bugzilla installation. It provides getter methods for various properties, such as the bug summary and status. To obtain a new Bug object, you must use the BugFactory class which provides a fluent interface for bug creation. Note that the BugFactory does not submit a report for you -- to actually add the created bug to your Bugzilla installation, you must use the ReportBug method.
    Author:
    Tom, Skywalker11 aka. Michael Pietsch (modified 2016/2017)

      • setStatus

        public void setStatus(String status)
        Sets the status of this Bug indicating whether it is open or closed. Since this field can be edited between installations, you may wish to check its legal values.

        If changing a bug's state from closed to open, the resolution must also be reset. Otherwise, the remote Bugzilla installation will throw an error. Clients must manually call clearResolution(). Since the status and resolution fields are customizable, this library cannot safely determine when to call this method automatically, so managing the state of the bug is the responsibility of the caller.

        Parameters:
        status - A String representing the status of this bug.
        See Also:
        setResolution(String)

      • getResolution

        public String getResolution()

        Returns:

        See Also:
        to retrieve a list of the defined resolutions for a specific installation.

      • setResolution

        public void setResolution(String resolution)
        Sets the resolution of this Bug. Since this field can be edited between installations, you may wish to check its legal values.

        If the status does not correspond to a closed value, this value is meaningless. Bugzilla allows the definition of custom workflows, so maintaining a correct correspondence between resolution and status is the responsibility of the caller.

        Parameters:
        resolution - A String representing the resolution of this bug.
        See Also:
        clearResolution()

      • clearResolution

        public void clearResolution()
        Removes any existing resolution for this Bug. Since a resolution can only be applied to a closed bug, depending on the workflow defined by the particular Bugzilla installation, changing a bug's status from closed to open requires the caller also invoke this method. Because of this customization capability, it is impossible to safely determine automatically when to clear a set resolution.
